# RoboLedger V5.2.19: High-Fidelity UI Audit & Parser Fixes

A comprehensive sweep to bring the V5 interface to "Stock Market" levels of dynamic polish while resolving critical parsing bugs. This includes layout expansion, structural dividers, live sort animations, and a functional audit of the settings drawer and parser engine.

## User Review Required

> [!CAUTION]
> **Parser Audit**: I will be modifying the core statement parsing logic to ensure Debits and Credits are correctly separated. This will affect all future imports.
> **Ref# Instability**: Enabling dynamic Ref# re-calculation means the "Ref#" column will change based on the current sort order (Always 001 at the top). If you require static persistent IDs, please let me know.

## Proposed Changes

### UI Logic (app.js)
- **Scale Expansion**: Increase all `max-width: 1060px` instances to **`1166px`** (+10%).
- **Dynamic Sorting**:
  - Enable Tabulator row animations where possible.
  - Fix Ref# formatter to strictly follow current sort index (`row.getPosition(true)`).
- **Settings & Theme**:
  - Default `UI_STATE.theme` to **'rainbow'**.
  - Re-wire [toggleSettings()](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js#181-182) and the settings drawer submit logic to ensure theme changes persist and trigger a full [render()](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js#36-41).
- **Auto-Cat Ticker**: Use a CSS transition on `.coa-tag` elements to create a "sliding/fading" update effect when categories change.

### Styling (system.css)
- **Header Dividers**: Add vertical separators (`border-right: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1)`) to grid headers.
- **Rainbow Default**: Ensure the `rainbow-theme` CSS variables are applied by default to the body/container.
- **Glass Refinement**: Ensure the 10% width increase doesn't break the backdrop-blur coverage.

### Core Logic (ledger/parser logic)
- **Parser Debug**: Investigate the statement parsing loop. Fix the logic that is currently bucketizing all amounts into "Credits". Implement a polarity check based on column headers (e.g., "Debit" vs "Credit") or amount signs.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Vertical Alignment Check**: Use a browser inspector or visual guide to ensure the left and right edges of the Header Card, Action Bar, and Switcher Bar are perfectly flush with each other.
2. **Standardization Check**: Confirm that resizing the window maintains the 1060px centered islanding for all elements in the stack.

